description= <LEFT> <SIZE:small>  Grapeseed, nestled northwest of Rosewood, has evolved from humble beginnings into a vibrant, gentrified town centered around Highway 60, opening it up to all of Knox Country. <LINE> <LINE> It offers a blend of modern luxury and historical charm. Despite its modest roots, Grapeseed now boasts luxurious accommodations next to its long-standing colonial library, with a beautiful walking path winding around the picturesque Grapeseed Lake between them. The town thrives on its unique personality and welcoming atmosphere. Though it may seem like just another small town, Grapeseed life is all about its friendly community. Come visit and experience the best of rural Kentucky!
